From: Codex <codex@openai.com>
Date: Sat, 9 May 2026 22:00:00 +0200
Subject: [PATCH] xilinx: avoid OSERDESE2 OFB null dereference

When an OSERDESE2 uses OQ and the output buffer lookup fails, OFB can be
unconnected. The existing fallback branch unconditionally dereferenced OFB
while checking for the OFB-to-ISERDESE2 loopback case, turning an unsupported
OQ fanout into a segfault during IOLOGIC packing.

Keep the loopback case limited to designs with a connected OFB net. Designs
with unsupported OQ fanout now report the intended packer error instead of
crashing.
---
 xilinx/pack_io_xc7.cc | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/xilinx/pack_io_xc7.cc b/xilinx/pack_io_xc7.cc
--- a/xilinx/pack_io_xc7.cc
+++ b/xilinx/pack_io_xc7.cc
@@ -868,7 +868,7 @@ void XC7Packer::pack_iologic()
                         used_oserdes_bels.insert(ctx->getBelByName(ctx->id(slave_bel_name)));
                     }
-                } else if (ofb->users.size() == 1 && ofb->users.at(0).cell->type == ctx->id("ISERDESE2")) {
+                } else if (!ofb_disconnected && ofb->users.size() == 1 && ofb->users.at(0).cell->type == ctx->id("ISERDESE2")) {
                     unconstrained_oserdes.insert(ci);
                 } else {
                     log_error("%s '%s' has illegal fanout on OQ or OFB output. This means that it is not connected to a corresponding OLOGIC BEL.\n", 
                 auto check_shiftin = [&] (NetInfo *shiftin) {
